thread.title: Rise, Brushing Aside Weak Chinese Export Data
thread.title_full: Stocks Rise, Brushing Aside Weak Chinese Export Data - WSJ

author: Chiara Albanese
title: Rise, Brushing Aside Weak Chinese Export Data
text:
Global stocks pushed higher Tuesday, brushing aside the latest set of weak economic data out of China.
The Stoxx Europe 600 index opened 1.4% higher, helped by a healthy gain in the Shanghai Composite Index amid buying late in the Asian session. Despite today’s gains of 2.9%, China’s stock market is still down roughly 43% from its June peak.
